<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The keys of the config are not handled the same in the class.
Everywhere lowercased keys are used except at hasOption($key).</p>

<p>Problem code:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
    /**
     * Is an option present?
     * 
     * @param  string $key 
     * @return bool
     */
    public function hasOption($key)
    {
        return in_array($key, $this-&gt;_optionKeys);
    }
</code></pre>

<p>Suggested fix:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
    /**
     * Is an option present?
     * 
     * @param  string $key 
     * @return bool
     */
    public function hasOption($key)
    {
        return in_array(strtolower($key), $this-&gt;_optionKeys);
    }
</code></pre>

